# ORIG TITLE    Italian ‘master’ Battiato hits the road . 
# ORIG CONTENT  Italian musician Franco Battiato is in the midst of a mini European tour to mark the release of his 28th album, Apriti Sesamo. Battiato, 68, started his career in the 1960s and his stand-out lyrics have made him a legend in his native Italy, earning him the nickname ‘The Master’. Euronews caught up with him after a live show in Brussels. 
